WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:01:29.470 --> 00:02:15.120  
1. At top of show:
Shostakovich, Symph. No, 7:

00:08:32.070 --> 00:08:36.400 
2. "Listen to the opening theme, for instance”:
Beginning through No. 2. (No entrance of oboe.)

00:10:20.530 --> 00:10:23.590
3.	"... just like Haydn, until it suddenly stumbles on a loud wrong note**:
First 4 bars, with upbeat (omit last note)

00:10:32.150 --> 00:10:34.150
4.	"... such a strong accent on it, to say nothing of a trill":
Violins: bar 4 (omit last note)

00:11:03.280 --> 00:11:07.280
5.	"... as in this little theme, which follows the one we just heard":
Tutti: one after No. 2, with upbt., for 4 bars (omit last
quarter)

00:11:19.750 --> 00:11:21.150  
6-A. "So once you hear the first phrase": 
Oboe alone:

00:11:25.150 --> 00:11:27.760 
6-B. "You expect the second one to be identical, only higher": 
Oboe [altered part]:

00:11:43.060 --> 00:11:48.060
7.	"... just enough to knock you off balance, like that tipsy clown":
Tutti: One after No. 2, with upbt., for 4 bars (omit last
quarter)

00:12:46.190 --> 00:12:55.470
8.	"... here is the first theme, with its harmonic switch":
Tutti:	No. 5, with upbt., for 8 bars (no trb.)

00:13:05.190 --> 00:13:08.190
9.	*... Shostakovich wrenches us into the new required key of B-flat":
Tutti:	No. 6, with upbt., for 2 bars

00:13:25.430 --> 00:13:34.990
10.	"... and see how the harmony jerks you from key to key":
Tutti:	No. 5, with upbt., through 2nd bar of No. 6

00:14:35.380 --> 00:14:45.049  
11.	"... little marching tune, whistled by the tiny, tinny piccolo":
Tutti:	No. 6 through 1 before No. 8 (omit last quarter)

00:15:18.390 --> 00:15:32.100
12.	"... solo violin, forcing out his .... tune over the .... brass section”:
Tutti:	No. 21 through 6 after 22 (omit last quarter)

00:15:55.000 --> 00:15:56.550
13.	"... trombone... Introduces this tune... with those pompous two notes”:
Trb. alone:	No. 21, with upbt.

00:16:15.970 --> 00:16:26.950 
14.	"... as though he*s skipped 50 bars..., and has come in too soon”:
Tutti:	No. 19, with upbt., to dbt. of 20

00:16:36.710 --> 00:16:44.970
15.	"... like Pluto in those cartoons”:
Tutti:	No. 20, with upbt., through 4th bar of No. 21

00:17:14.210 --> 00:22:26.000 
16.	"... listen to this... first movement... by Shostakovich”:
Full performance of MVT. I

00:23:07.300 --> 00:23:27.990 
17.	"It opens with this clarinet solo”:
Tutti:	MVT. II - beginning to dbt. of 3 before No. 29

00:23:55.210 --> 00:24:14.670
18.	"... the strings play strange, yearning waves of melody”:
Tutti: MVT. II - No. 35 to dbt. of No. 36

00:25:39.210 --> 00:33:15.840  
19. "So here is the very unsymphonic second movement”:
Full performance of MVT. II

00:34:41.600 --> 00:35:09.820
20.	"... trumpet blares out... Spanish-type tune, like bull-fight music”:
Tutti: MVT. Ill- No. 57 to dbt. of one before No. 59

00:36:18.660 --> 00:36:34.880 
21.	"...as if to introduce some great tragic utterance”:
Trombones:	MVT. IV - first 6 bars

00:36:55.000 --> 00:37:06.000
22.	"...bassoon solo... very mournful and tragic”:
Bassoon alone: MVT. IV - first 12 notes

00:37:45.160 --> 00:37:58.729  
23.	"... there is this recitation by the cellos and basses”:
Cellos and Basses:	Beethoven Symph. No. 9, Finale:

00:38:09.940 --> 00:38:11.599 
24.	”... bassoon doing... same thing, even in the same key”:
Bassoon:	MVT. IV - first 2 notes

00:38:40.890 --> 00:38:44.940  
25-A.	”... this same mournful bassoon, without so much as
drawing breath”:
Bassoon:	hold C-flat

00:38:48.920 --> 00:39:11.270
25-B.	”... slyly sneaks into a saucy little dance-tune”:
Tutti:	MVT. V - No. 70 to No. 71

00:40:22.760 --> 00:51:32.870 
26. ”Happy listening! And happy birthday, Dmitri Shostakovich”: 
Full performance, MVTS. Ill, IV and V